This paper is primarily focused on designing hardware-efficient ConvNets for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses neural architecture search (NAS) and differentiable NAS methods, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the network for runtime constraints, which is related to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing efficient hardware, which is related to the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
